  "prompt": "How do I print an application form on the OJAS website?",
  "response": "To print an application form from the OJAS (Online Job Application System) website, follow these general steps:\n\n1. **Visit the OJAS Website:** Open your web browser and go to the official OJAS website.\n\n2. **Login to Your Account:** If you have already applied for a job, you need to log in using your login credentials (Application Number and Date of Birth).\n\n3. **Access Your Application:** After logging in, look for the section that allows you to view your submitted applications. This could be labeled something like \"My Applications\" or \"Application Status.\"\n\n4. **Select the Application:** Find the specific application form you want to print. There should be an option to view or print it.\n\n5. **Print the Application:** Once you have the application form open, look for a \"Print\" button or option. You can usually also print the page by using your browser's print function (Ctrl + P for Windows or Command + P for Mac).\n\n6. **Check Print Preview:** Before confirming the print, check the print preview to ensure that the application form is formatted correctly.\n\n7. **Print the Document:** Once everything looks good, proceed to print your application form.\n\nIf you encounter issues or if the steps vary due to changes in the website's interface, refer to any help or FAQ section on the OJAS website, or reach out to their customer support for assistance.",
